QR Code Payment Generator (Flask + PayPal)

Welcome! 🚀 This is a simple Flask project that generates a QR code for PayPal payments based on the amount you enter. Just type in an amount, hit the button, and get a QR code that directs you to PayPal for payment!

📌 Features:

Enter any amount you want to pay.

Generates a PayPal payment QR code instantly.

Simple and easy-to-use web interface.

Works with any device that can scan QR codes.

🔧 How to Set Up

1️⃣ Install Dependencies

Make sure you have Python installed, then install Flask and qrcode:

pip install flask qrcode[pil]

2️⃣ Run the App

Save the Python script as app.py and run:

python app.py

3️⃣ Open in Browser

Once the app is running, open your browser and go to:

http://127.0.0.1:5000/

💰 How It Works

Enter the amount you want to pay.

Click the "Generate QR Code" button.

Scan the QR code to proceed to PayPal.

🛠 Customize Your PayPal Email

In app.py, replace this line with your actual PayPal business email:

PAYPAL_EMAIL = "your-paypal-email@example.com"

🌟 Why Use This?

No need to manually type PayPal links.

Quick and easy for customers to pay.

Great for small businesses, freelancers, and online sellers!

